<br>
I will not attempt the kill without at least 30 people in the proper level range, and not without<br>
2 Bards<br>
1 level 50+ mage<br>
1 person as second in command, who has attended several dragon raids (I haven't, I'm only doing this to get it going &lt;grins&gt;)<br>
<br>
And, the more, the better. Above is minimum.<br>
<br>
Course, we need the standard, clerics etc. But the above - we might have to go outside the federation for a bard. I don't know, but those resist songs are very, very nice. The mage will need to be able to get an early start - I want everyone on the raid to have both those summoned resist shoulder pieces, and that summoned resist shield. That includes healers, casters, etc. <br>
<br>
Start time - 10pm EST. That is START time. I want to be moving in no later than 10:15, and I want people to gather at 8pm EST. PST folks can filter in later than that - but we are done with stuff and moving at 10:15, no ifs, no ands, no buts about it. If we can't be moving by 10:15, we cancel.<br>
<br>
Loot - one person, designated in advance for each guild, will roll for each item of interest. Whatever federation guild wins, they can then decide which of their members that item goes to, by whatever means they want. (With one additional limit, detailed below) This means a maximum of 9 folks rolling. Crew of Destiny is considered Federation by me at least, and since I'm raid leader - they are in. I want to see a representative from every federation guild here - even if its only one. Your presence, even as a token, is greatly desired. All Federation guilds are family, and your presence is wanted.<br>
<br>
Now, this last is most important - Guild leaders, recruit heavily for this. Next Thursday, March 7th, in my sign up thread, which I will put up in the next day or two - if I don't see 30 folks from the various guilds all signed up as going to be there, with name, level, class and guild, then it gets cancelled Thursday night. (Watch - all this prep work, and neither dragon will be up). You can get the sign ups within your guild actually, and you post a list of who will definatly be attending all in one consolidated guild post if you want. This is carved in stone - no 30 names (and thats 30 names of folks who will be fighting the Dragon, not any extra buffers, vermin control, etc) on Thursday by 9:30 pm EST, and no raid.<br>
<br>
I would really like for a full group of higher levels to be present, whose job would be to keep the fight between the raid members, and Lord Nagafen, or Lady Vox. I.E, they kill the adds. <br>
<br>
Anything that I am missing? Anything that needs to be added? This doesn't cover the tactics (I'm going to go by the link I posted earlier, which seems pretty good). <br>
<br>
Thoughts, contributions, etc?<br>
<br>
